{ A logical move, going for the bishop pair since our knight on e7 now blocks the queen's vision of the h4-square. However, since this knight will have moved 3 times just to trade itself off, it doesn't bother us very much. }
6... c5
{ Phase two of our plan! If White plays slowly, we respond quickly in the centre. }
7. Nxf5 { White follows through with their plan of taking our bishop. } 7...
Nxf5
{ Don't even think about  7...exf5  ,  committing positional suicide.   This kind of variation shows the early ... Ne7 has multiple potential avenues into the game. If White steers it towards f5, we will happily oblige. }
8. c3
{ White has to do something about the weakness on d4.  8.dxc5  Nc6  is a little better than passively defending d4 forever, but it's still quite bad for White.   We will comfortably regain the c-pawn with continued pressure. We didn't even need to struggle to develop. }
8... cxd4 9. cxd4
{ 9.g4  is already necessary to avoid getting rolled over in the centre right away, but it only creates another weakness. Besides, an amateur will almost certainly not think to play this way.  Nh4  10.cxd4  h5  A fantastic move, activating the h8-rook and ruining White's pawn structure.  11.gxh5  Nc6  We don't care that we're down a pawn one bit. White's king will never find shelter. }
9... Nc6
{ Do I need to memorize exactly when to start with ...Nc6 and when to first capture on d4?   Absolutely not. There are sometimes subtle differences, but as long as you make sure White can't advantageously capture on c5, it shouldn't matter much. The main thing is to maintain pressure on this square. }
10. Be3 Qb6
{ By now, this ...Nc6, ...Qb6 construction should be permanently seared into your memory, especially in lines where White plays c3. }
11. Qd2
{ A move attempting to keep both weaknesses defended. But White is stretched too thin. }
11... Bb4 { We can already take on d4, but I prefer developing! } 12. Nc3 Ncxd4
{ This has been a disaster for white, who has lost an important central pawn with no compensation. Next can be ...Nxe3, ...O-O and rooks to the centre. }
