{ We have another dynamite variation because White has the immediate threat of smothered mate in one move! }
5... Ndf6
{ It's important to remember to use this knight, giving our king some breathing room on d7. After 5... Ngf6  6. Nd6# the e-pawn is pinned and cannot capture the knight. Don't let this happen to you! }
6. Nf3 Nxe4
{ Whenever we have the chance to trade off White's central knight, we go for it. }
7. Qxe4 Nf6 { Who can resist developing a piece with tempo? } 8. Qd3
{ The best square for the queen.  8.Qh4  simply misplaces the queen on the side of the board and after  Bf5  and ...e6 next, Black has no problems. }
8... Bg4
{ In the Classical Variation and Two Knights Variation whenever we can acheive this ...Bg4/...e6 setup, we are doing very well! }
9. Be2 { White wants to castle quickly. } 9... e6 10. O-O Bd6
{ White has made normal opening moves but has posed us no problems, and will likely lose another tempo on the queen after ...Bf5. The next moves can be ...O-O and ...Qc7 @@StartBracket@@with the threat of ...Bxf3 and ...Bxh2+@@EndBracket@@ and eventually deploying Old Faithful. }
