8... exf6 9. d5 Nb4
{ Don't panic - we aren't in any danger here. Next we can recapture the d-pawn with a great position. }
10. dxe6 { Or, White can take our piece, losing the game! } 10... Nd3+
{ This is a devastating check. The difference in this line is the since the knight sits in the way of White's bishop, our knight can't be captured. }
11. Kd2 Nxb2+ { Adiscovered check on the king, winning the queen. } 12. Kc2
Nxd1
{ Justice is sweet. White is punished for their greed and for misplacing the knight on e2. }
