{ It's time to ask the b5-bishop to announce its intentions. } 7. Ba4
{ 7.Bxd7+  would only help us develop.  Qxd7  8.Nf3  Nxd5  As in most lines when we've managed to exchange of White's light-squared bishop, we have absoutely no problems.   Black may even be better here due to the bishop pair. }
7... b5 { We don't need a second invitation to hit the bishop a second time. }
8. Bb3 Bb7 9. Nf3
{ White has no good way to prevent our plan of ...b4.  9.a3  stops ...b4, but we are still winning the pawn after  Nc5  . }
9... b4 { Deflecting a defender of the d5-pawn. } 10. Na4 Nxd5
{ In view of White'sIQP and sidelined a4-knight, Black is better. } *

