26. Kg3 { Is Keith ready to proceed with the minority attack? } 26... Rg8
{ There's no law that states all of your moves need to be towards the queenside. Keith is looking for ...h5 in order to create another weakness.   Black isn't ready for  26...b4  yet since  27.axb4  axb4  28.cxb4  Rxb4  29.fxe6  would allow the centre to collapse. }
27. Kf4 h5
{ This is quite advanced, but in endgames, the Principle of Two Weaknesses says that often creating a single weakness isn't enough to win.  It's hard to say if Keith was thinking about winning, or just doing a bit of harmless probing in this position, but Keith is clearly aiming for the creation of a pawn weakness in White's camp on both the queenside and kingside. }
