[FEN "2rr2k1/1p2bpp1/p3p2p/n2n4/2BP4/1P2BN1P/1P3PP1/2R1R1K1 w - - 0 19"]
[SetUp "1"]

19. Bxd5 { White has just captured on d5. What is the best response? } 19...
Rxc1
{ 19...Rxd5  would drop a rook!  20.Rxc8+  If you played   19...exd5  I refer you to the previous puzzle. }
20. Rxc1 Rxd5 { Of course, recapturing with the piece! } 21. Rc3
{ Defending the b-pawn. } 21... Nc6
{ Black now maximizes pressure on d4, keeping White's pieces passive. The weakness of the d-pawn allows Black to maximize the position, create further weaknesses, and eventually win material. }
